.TH FOOMATIC-GETPJLOPTIONS 8 "2001-05-07" "Foomatic Project"
.SH NAME
foomatic-getpjloptions \- <put a short description here>
.SH SYNOPSIS
.BI foomatic-getpjloptions device

.BI foomatic-getpjloptions hostname\ port

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B foomatic-getpjloptions
Reads the PJL options from local (parallel, USB, serial, ...) or remote
(only socket, LPD is not bi-directional) printers to standard output. The
output can be piped into foomatic-addpjloptions to add options to the database.


.SS Options
.TP 10
.BI device
where a local printer is connected, e.g. /dev/lp0, /dev/usb/lp0. Have
your parallel port in EPP/bi-directional mode (see your BIOS
settings).

.TP 10
.BI hostname
Host name or IP of a network printer (HP JetDirect, Socket, ...)

.TP 10
.BI port
Port on which your network printer listens.


.\".SH SEE ALSO
.\".IR foomatic-XXX (1),

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B foomatic-getpjloptions
returns ???

.SH AUTHOR
Manfred Wassmann <\fImanolo@NCC-1701.B.Shuttle.de\fR> for the foomatic
project using output from the associated binary.

.SH BUGS
Uni-directional protocols as remote LPD are not supported..

